@ryoppippi - I dug into this issue a bit with Claude's assistance (Opus 4.1). Here's the summary of issue(s), implications, and fixes required...
Subagent Token Tracking Fix Documentation
Problem Statement (GitHub Issue #313)
Users are experiencing significant discrepancies between actual Claude Code usage and what ccusage reports when using subagents (Task tool). The issue manifests as:

Users hitting 5-hour token limits while ccusage shows only 10-20% usage
Subagent tokens not appearing in daily, session, or block reports
Total usage appearing drastically lower than actual consumption
Live monitoring not updating while subagents are running

User Impact

"I hit the limit while ccusage was showing only about 10% usage" - @GiampaoloGabba
"Usually my token count for a block is 12-20m before limits but with sub agents I'm at 4m tokens before hitting limit" - @nhoss2

Root Cause Analysis
After examining actual JSONL files from Claude Code sessions with subagents, the root cause has TWO critical parts:
Part 1: Missing Sidechain Entries
Entries marked with "isSidechain": true are the actual subagent activity and are currently being parsed but not filtered correctly.
Part 2: Missing Tool Result Summary
The toolUseResult field contains the aggregated total of all subagent tokens and is being ignored.
The problem is BOTH:

Individual subagent entries (isSidechain: true) - 1,086,368 tokens in our example
Summary in tool result (toolUseResult.totalTokens) - 38,203 tokens reported back

Note: The discrepancy between individual entries (1M tokens) and the summary (38K tokens) suggests the summary might be excluding cache tokens or only counting certain operations.
