Complete breakdown available - Full usage details are preserved

Proposed Solution
The fix requires handling BOTH types of subagent data:
1. Schema Extension (src/_types.ts)
Add new schema for tool use results:
/**
 * Zod schema for subagent/tool use result data
 */
export const toolUseResultSchema = z.object({
  content: z.array(z.object({
    type: z.string(),
    text: z.string().optional(),
  })).optional(),
  totalDurationMs: z.number().optional(),
  totalTokens: z.number().optional(),
  totalToolUseCount: z.number().optional(),
  usage: z.object({
    input_tokens: z.number(),
    output_tokens: z.number(),
    cache_creation_input_tokens: z.number().optional(),
    cache_read_input_tokens: z.number().optional(),
    service_tier: z.string().optional(),
  }).optional(),
});

// Update main usage data schema
export const usageDataSchema = z.object({
  // ... existing fields ...
  isSidechain: z.boolean().optional(), // Add this field to identify subagent entries
  message: z.object({
    // ... existing message fields ...
  }),
  toolUseResult: toolUseResultSchema.optional(), // Add this field for summaries
  // ... rest of schema ...
});
2. Critical: Model-Aware Cost Calculation
Subagents can use different models! The parser MUST respect the model field in each entry:
// CRITICAL: Use the correct model for cost calculation
const model = entry.message?.model || 'unknown';
const isSubagent = entry.isSidechain === true;

if (entry.message?.usage) {
  // Calculate cost using THE ENTRY'S MODEL, not session default!
  const cost = await calculateCostForModel(
    entry.message.usage,
    model  // ← This could be Sonnet even if main is Opus!
  );

  if (isSubagent) {
    subagentCosts[model] = (subagentCosts[model] || 0) + cost;
  } else {
    mainAgentCosts[model] = (mainAgentCosts[model] || 0) + cost;
  }
}
3. Parser Update (src/data-loader.ts)
Modify the JSONL parsing logic to handle ALL three token sources AND respect model differences:
// In parseJsonlFile or similar function
for (const line of lines) {
  try {
    const entry = JSON.parse(line);

    // UPDATED: Check if this is a sidechain/subagent entry
    const isSubagent = entry.isSidechain === true;

    // Check for regular message tokens (existing logic)
    if (entry.message?.usage) {
      const usage = entry.message.usage;
      const tokens = usage.input_tokens + usage.output_tokens + 
                     (usage.cache_creation_input_tokens || 0) +
                     (usage.cache_read_input_tokens || 0);

      if (isSubagent) {
        subagentTokens += tokens;
        entry.isSubagentUsage = true;
      } else {
        regularTokens += tokens;
      }
    }

    // NEW: Check for subagent/tool result summary tokens
    if (entry.toolUseResult?.totalTokens) {
      // This is the summary - might be different from sum of individuals
      // Use it for validation or as a separate metric
      subagentSummaryTokens += entry.toolUseResult.totalTokens;
      entry.isSubagentSummary = true;
    } else if (entry.toolUseResult?.usage) {
      // Detailed breakdown in tool result
      const usage = entry.toolUseResult.usage;
      const tokens = 
        usage.input_tokens + 
        usage.output_tokens + 
        (usage.cache_creation_input_tokens || 0) +
        (usage.cache_read_input_tokens || 0);
      subagentSummaryTokens += tokens;
      entry.isSubagentSummary = true;
    }

    processedEntries.push(entry);
  } catch {
    // Skip invalid lines
  }
}
4. Enhanced Reporting
Add visibility for subagent usage AND model breakdown in reports:
