I suspect that if settings.json is deemed bad/invalid, it doesn't load it at all, and instead reverts to default values on all configuration settings, which may then apply the 30-day history default, and remove files. Just a guess, but that would explain how/why cc would delete these files down to just prior 30-day history even if you have modified cleanupPeriodDays.
